strict size ordering: larger bigger smaller\n    (larger d6 d5) (larger d6 d4) (larger d6 d3) (larger d6 d2) (larger d6 d1)\n    (larger d5 d4) (larger d5 d3) (larger d5 d2) (larger d5 d1)\n    (larger d4 d3) (larger d4 d2) (larger d4 d1)\n    (larger d3 d2) (larger d3 d1)\n    (larger d2 d1)\n\n    ;; time starts at t0\n    (now t0)\n\n    ;; contiguous successor chain for exactly 63 single-step moves\n    (next t0 t1) (next t1 t2) (next t2 t3) (next t3 t4) (next t4 t5) (next t5 t6) (next t6 t7) (next t7 t8)\n    (next t8 t9) (next t9 t10) (next t10 t11) (next t11 t12) (next t12 t13) (next t13 t14) (next t14 t15) (next t15 t16)\n    (next t16 t17) (next t17 t18) (next t18 t19) (next t19 t20) (next t20 t21) (next t21 t22) (next t22 t23) (next t23 t24)\n    (next t24 t25) (next t25 t26) (next t26 t27) (next t27 t28) (next t28 t29) (next t29 t30) (next t30 t31) (next t31 t32)\n    (next t32 t33) (next t33 t34) (next t34 t35) (next t35 t36) (next t36 t37) (next t37 t38) (next t38 t39) (next t39 t40)\n    (next t40 t41) (next t41 t42) (next t42 t43) (next t43 t44) (next t44 t45) (next t45 t46) (next t46 t47) (next t47 t48)\n    (next t48 t49) (next t49 t50) (next t50 t51) (next t51 t52) (next t52 t53) (next t53 t54) (next t54 t55) (next t55 t56)\n    (next t56 t57) (next t57 t58) (next t58 t59) (next t59 t60) (next t60 t61) (next t61 t62) (next t62 t63)\n  )\n\n  (:goal (and\n    ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  ;; disk and peg share a common supertype 'support' so a disk can be on either a disk or a peg\n  (:types disk peg - support time)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk directly on a support (support = disk or peg)\n    (on ?d - disk ?s - support)\n\n    ;; nothing on top of a support (either a peg or a disk)\n    (clear ?s - support)\n\n    ;; size ordering: ?big is strictly larger than ?small\n    (larger ?big - disk ?small - disk)\n\n    ;; discrete time bookkeeping\n    (now ?t - time)\n    (next ?t1 - time ?t2 - time)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto an empty peg\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - support ?to - peg ?t - time ?t2 - time)\n    :precondition (and\n      (now ?t)\n      (next ?t ?t2)\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)           ; disk being moved must have nothing on top\n      (clear ?to)          ; destination peg must have nothing on top (either empty or top)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)        ; the support we removed the disk from becomes clear on top\n      (not (clear ?to))    ; destination peg no longer clear (now has ?d on top)\n      (not (now ?t))\n      (now ?t2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto an empty disk (requires size ordering)\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - support ?to - disk ?t - time ?t2 - time)\n    :precondition (and\n      (now ?t)\n      (next ?t ?t2)\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)           ; disk being moved must have nothing on top\n      (clear ?to)          ; destination disk must have nothing on top\n      (larger ?to ?d)      ; cannot place larger on smaller: destination must be larger\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)        ; the support we removed the disk from becomes clear on top\n      (not (clear ?to))    ; destination disk no longer clear (now has ?d on top)\n      (not (now ?t))\n      (now ?t2)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi6-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi-6)\n\n  (:objects\n    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 - disk\n    pegL pegM pegR - peg\n    t0 t1 t2 t3 t4 t5 t6 t7 t8 t9 t10 t11 t12 t13 t14 t15\n    t16 t17 t18 t19 t20 t21 t22 t23 t24 t25 t26 t27 t28 t29 t30 t31\n    t32 t33 t34 t35 t36 t37 t38 t39 t40 t41 t42 t43 t44 t45 t46 t47\n    t48 t49 t50 t51 t52 t53 t54 t55 t56 t57 t58 t59 t60 t61 t62 t63 - time\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; initial stack on middle peg: top d1, then d2, d3, d4, d5, d6 (d6 directly on pegM)\n    (on d1 d2)\n    (on d2 d3)\n    (on d3 d4)\n    (on d4 d5)\n    (on d5 d6)\n    (on d6 pegM)\n\n    ;; clear markers: top disk and empty pegs\n    (clear d1)\n    (clear pegL)\n    (clear pegR)\n\n    ;; size ordering: larger X Y means X is larger than Y (d6 largest, d1 smallest)\n    (larger d6 d5) (larger d6 d4) (larger d6 d3) (larger d6 d2) (larger d6 d1)\n    (larger d5 d4) (larger d5 d3) (larger d5 d2) (larger d5 d1)\n    (larger d4 d3) (larger d4 d2) (larger d4 d1)\n    (larger d3 d2) (larger d3 d1)\n    (larger d2 d1)\n\n    ;; time start\n    (now t0)\n\n    ;; explicit discrete time succession for 63 moves (t0..t63)\n    (next t0 t1) (next t1 t2) (next t2 t3) (next t3 t4) (next t4 t5) (next t5 t6) (next t6 t7) (next t7 t8)\n    (next t8 t9) (next t9 t10) (next t10 t11) (next t11 t12) (next t12 t13) (next t13 t14) (next t14 t15) (next t15 t16)\n    (next t16 t17) (next t17 t18) (next t18 t19) (next t19 t20) (next t20 t21) (next t21 t22) (next t22 t23) (next t23 t24)\n    (next t24 t25) (next t25 t26) (next t26 t27) (next t27 t28) (next t28 t29) (next t29 t30) (next t30 t31) (next t31 t32)\n    (next t32 t33) (next t33 t34) (next t34 t35) (next t35 t36) (next t36 t37) (next t37 t38) (next t38 t39) (next t39 t40)\n    (next t40 t41) (next t41 t42) (next t42 t43) (next t43 t44) (next t44 t45) (next t45 t46) (next t46 t47) (next t47 t48)\n    (next t48 t49) (next t49 t50) (next t50 t51) (next t51 t52) (next t52 t53) (next t53 t54) (next t54 t55) (next t55 t56)\n    (next t56 t57) (next t57 t58) (next t58 t59) (next t59 t60) (next t60 t61) (next t61 t62) (next t62 t63)\n  )\n\n  (:goal (and\n    ;; desired final stack on right peg: top d1, then d2, d3, d4, d5, d6 (d6 directly on pegR)\n    (on d1 d2)\n    (on d2 d3)\n    (on d3 d4)\n    (on d4 d5)\n    (on d5 d6)\n    (on d6 pegR)\n\n    ;; final clears: top disk and empty pegs left and middle\n    (clear d1)\n    (clear pegL)\n    (clear pegM)\n\n    ;; NATURAL-PLAN sas_plan_1
------------------------------
Mapping: d1=A (smallest), d2=B, d3=C, d4=D, d5=E, d6=F (largest).
Pegs: pegl = Left, pegm = Middle, pegr = Right.
Each step advances the global time pointer by one time step; I report the timestamp tX  tY and duration = 1 time unit.

1. t0  t1 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B to Left peg.
2. t1  t2 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk C to Right peg.
3. t2  t3 (1 time unit): Move disk A from Left peg onto disk B.
4. t3  t4 (1 time unit): Move disk C from disk D to Left peg.
5. t4  t5 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk D.
6. t5  t6 (1 time unit): Move disk B from Right peg onto disk C.
7. t6  t7 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk D onto disk B.
8. t7  t8 (1 time unit): Move disk D from disk E to Right peg.
9. t8  t9 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk D.
10. t9  t10 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk C onto disk E.
11. t10  t11 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk D onto disk B.
12. t11  t12 (1 time unit): Move disk C from Left peg onto disk D.
13. t12  t13 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B to Left peg.
14. t13  t14 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk E onto disk C.
15. t14  t15 (1 time unit): Move disk A from Left peg onto disk B.
16. t15  t16 (1 time unit): Move disk E from disk F to Left peg.
17. t16  t17 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk F.
18. t17  t18 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk C onto disk E.
19. t18  t19 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk F onto disk B.
20. t19  t20 (1 time unit): Move disk C from disk D onto disk F.
21. t20  t21 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk D.
22. t21  t22 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk E onto disk C.
23. t22  t23 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk D onto disk B.
24. t23  t24 (1 time unit): Move disk D from Right peg onto disk E.
25. t24  t25 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk D.
26. t25  t26 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk C to Right peg.
27. t26  t27 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk D onto disk B.
28. t27  t28 (1 time unit): Move disk C from disk F onto disk D.
29. t28  t29 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk F.
30. t29  t30 (1 time unit): Move disk B from Right peg onto disk C.
31. t30  t31 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk F onto disk B.
32. t31  t32 (1 time unit): Move disk F from Middle peg to Right peg.
33. t32  t33 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk F.
34. t33  t34 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk C to Middle peg.
35. t34  t35 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk F onto disk B.
36. t35  t36 (1 time unit): Move disk C from disk D onto disk F.
37. t36  t37 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk D.
38. t37  t38 (1 time unit): Move disk B from Middle peg onto disk C.
39. t38  t39 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk D onto disk B.
40. t39  t40 (1 time unit): Move disk D from disk E to Middle peg.
41. t40  t41 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk D.
42. t41  t42 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk C onto disk E.
43. t42  t43 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk D onto disk B.
44. t43  t44 (1 time unit): Move disk C from disk F onto disk D.
45. t44  t45 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk F.
46. t45  t46 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk E onto disk C.
47. t46  t47 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk F onto disk B.
48. t47  t48 (1 time unit): Move disk E from Left peg onto disk F.
49. t48  t49 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B to Left peg.
50. t49  t50 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk C onto disk E.
51. t50  t51 (1 time unit): Move disk A from Left peg onto disk B.
52. t51  t52 (1 time unit): Move disk C from disk D to Left peg.
53. t52  t53 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B onto disk D.
54. t53  t54 (1 time unit): Move disk B from disk E onto disk C.

56. t55  t56 (1 time unit): Move disk D from Middle peg onto disk E.

59. t58  t59 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk D onto disk B.
60. t59  t60 (1 time unit): Move disk C from Left peg onto disk D.
61. t60  t61 (1 time unit): Move disk A from disk B to Left peg.
62. t61  t62 (1 time unit): Move disk B from Middle peg onto disk C.
63. t62  t63 (1 time unit): Move disk A from Left peg onto disk B.

Completion: after step 63 (now t63), the full stack A (top)  B  C  D  E  F (bottom) is on the Right peg, Middle and Left pegs are empty, and the plan used 63 unit moves as required.
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 6 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.
The left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 6 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.
The left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
; Domain: pddl_orchestrator
; Comment: The specification required handling moves of the top disk from one peg to another, enforcing size ordering,
; and accounted for the need to know whether a disk was directly on a peg or on another disk. To reconcile the
; typing/union issue (a disk's support can be either a peg or a disk) without nonstandard union types, this domain
; defines separate predicates on-peg and on-disk and provides four move actions that cover the four combinations:
; (disk on peg) -> (to empty peg), (disk on peg) -> (to peg with top disk),
; (disk on disk) -> (to empty peg), (disk on disk) -> (to peg with top disk).
; This ensures all state updates (top and empty predicates) are explicit and that illegal moves (placing larger on smaller)
; are prevented by preconditions. No bookkeeping/penalty constructs were added.

(define (domain pddl_orchestrator)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg)

  (:predicates
    (disk ?d - disk)
    (peg ?p - peg)

    ; direct support relations:
    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)     ; disk ?d is directly on peg ?p
    (on-disk ?d - disk ?under - disk) ; disk ?d is directly on disk ?under

    ; top-of-peg: the disk that is currently on the top of the peg (if peg non-empty)
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)

    ; whether a peg is currently empty (true exactly when there are no disks on that peg)
    (empty ?p - peg)

    ; size relation: smaller ?small ?big is true iff ?small is strictly smaller than ?big
    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk)
  )

  ; Move a disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.
  (:action move-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on-peg ?d ?pfrom)
                    (top ?d ?pfrom)
                    (empty ?pto)
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on-peg ?d ?pfrom))
              (on-peg ?d ?pto)

              (not (top ?d ?pfrom))
              (top ?d ?pto)

              (not (empty ?pto))
              (empty ?pfrom)
            )
  )

  ; Move a disk that is directly on a peg to a peg whose top is disk ?t (must be larger).
  (:action move-peg-to-nonempty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on-peg ?d ?pfrom)
                    (top ?d ?pfrom)
                    (top ?t ?pto)
                    (smaller ?d ?t)
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on-peg ?d ?pfrom))
              (on-disk ?d ?t)

              (not (top ?t ?pto))
              (top ?d ?pto)

              (not (top ?d ?pfrom))
              (empty ?pfrom)
            )
  )

  ; Move a disk that is directly on another disk (?under) to an empty peg.
  (:action move-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on-disk ?d ?under)
                    (top ?d ?pfrom)
                    (empty ?pto)
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on-disk ?d ?under))
              (on-peg ?d ?pto)

              (not (top ?d ?pfrom))
              (top ?d ?pto)

              ; the disk under becomes the new top of the source peg
              (top ?under ?pfrom)

              (not (empty ?pto))
            )
  )

  ; Move a disk that is directly on another disk (?under) to a peg whose top is disk ?t (must be larger).
  (:action move-disk-to-nonempty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on-disk ?d ?under)
                    (top ?d ?pfrom)
                    (top ?t ?pto)
                    (smaller ?d ?t)
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on-disk ?d ?under))
              (on-disk ?d ?t)

              (not (top ?t ?pto))
              (top ?d ?pto)

              (not (top ?d ?pfrom))
              (top ?under ?pfrom)
            )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
; Problem: six-disk Tower of Hanoi, all disks start on the middle peg.
; Comment: The user specification required six disks all stacked on the middle peg (peg-middle) with left and right empty,
; and the goal of all disks stacked on the right peg (peg-right) in correct order. All natural-language preferences were
; treated as hard constraints; no penalty or bookkeeping shortcuts were added.

(define (problem pddl_orchestrator-problem)
  (:domain pddl_orchestrator)

  (:objects
    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 - disk
    peg-left peg-middle peg-right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ; typing facts (optional but explicit)
    (disk d1) (disk d2) (disk d3) (disk d4) (disk d5) (disk d6)
    (peg peg-left) (peg peg-middle) (peg peg-right)

    ; initial stack: all six disks on the middle peg in order (d6 bottom ... d1 top)
    (on-peg d6 peg-middle)
    (on-disk d5 d6)
    (on-disk d4 d5)
    (on-disk d3 d4)
    (on-disk d2 d3)
    (on-disk d1 d2)

    ; top-of-peg facts: top disk on the middle peg is d1; left and right are empty
    (top d1 peg-middle)
    (empty peg-left)
    (empty peg-right)
    ; peg-middle is not marked empty (no empty predicate for it)

    ; size ordering: smaller relations (strict). d1 < d2 < ... < d6
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6)
    (smaller d5 d6)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ; all six disks stacked on the right peg in correct order (d6 bottom, then d5, ..., d1 top)
    (on-peg d6 peg-right)
    (on-disk d5 d6)
    (on-disk d4 d5)
    (on-disk d3 d4)
    (on-disk d2 d3)
    (on-disk d1 d2)

    ; explicitly enforce the top-of-peg fact for the final stack
    (top d1 peg-right)

    ; explicitly enforce that the left and middle pegs are empty in the terminal condition
    (empty peg-left)
    (empty peg-middle)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
; Domain: pddl_orchestrator
; Comment: The specification required handling moves of the top disk from one peg to another, enforcing size ordering,
; and accounted for the need to know whether a disk was directly on a peg or on another disk. To reconcile the

    "pddl_domain": "; Domain: pddl_orchestrator\n; Comment: The specification required handling moves of the top disk from one peg to another, enforcing size ordering,\n; and accounted for the need to know whether a disk was directly on a peg or on another disk. To reconcile the\n; typing/union issue (a disk's support can be either a peg or a disk) without nonstandard union types, this domain\n; defines separate predicates on-peg and on-disk and provides four move actions that cover the four combinations:\n; (disk on peg) -> (to empty peg), (disk on peg) -> (to peg with top disk),\n; (disk on disk) -> (to empty peg), (disk on disk) -> (to peg with top disk).\n; This ensures all state updates (top and empty predicates) are explicit and that illegal moves (placing larger on smaller)\n; are prevented by preconditions. No bookkeeping/penalty constructs were added.\n\n(define (domain pddl_orchestrator)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (disk ?d - disk)\n    (peg ?p - peg)\n\n    ; direct support relations:\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)     ; disk ?d is directly on peg ?p\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?under - disk) ; disk ?d is directly on disk ?under\n\n    ; top-of-peg: the disk that is currently on the top of the peg (if peg non-empty)\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ; whether a peg is currently empty (true exactly when there are no disks on that peg)\n    (empty ?p - peg)\n\n    ; size relation: smaller ?small ?big is true iff ?small is strictly smaller than ?big\n    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk)\n  )\n\n  ; Move a disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on-peg ?d ?pfrom)\n                    (top ?d ?pfrom)\n                    (empty ?pto)\n                  )\n    :effect (and\n              (not (on-peg ?d ?pfrom))\n              (on-peg ?d ?pto)\n\n              (not (top ?d ?pfrom))\n              (top ?d ?pto)\n\n              (not (empty ?pto))\n              (empty ?pfrom)\n            )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a disk that is directly on a peg to a peg whose top is disk ?t (must be larger).\n  (:action move-peg-to-nonempty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on-peg ?d ?pfrom)\n                    (top ?d ?pfrom)\n                    (top ?t ?pto)\n                    (smaller ?d ?t)\n                  )\n    :effect (and\n              (not (on-peg ?d ?pfrom))\n              (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n              (not (top ?t ?pto))\n              (top ?d ?pto)\n\n              (not (top ?d ?pfrom))\n              (empty ?pfrom)\n            )\n  )\n\n  ; the disk under becomes the new top of the source peg\n              (top ?under ?pfrom)\n\n              (not (empty ?pto))\n            )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a disk that is directly on another disk (?under) to a peg whose top is disk ?t (must be larger).\n  (:action move-disk-to-nonempty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on-disk ?d ?under)\n                    (top ?d ?pfrom)\n                    (top ?t ?pto)\n                    (smaller ?d ?t)\n                  )\n    :effect (and\n              (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n              (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n              (not (top ?t ?pto))\n              (top ?d ?pto)\n\n              (not (top ?d ?pfrom))\n              (top ?under ?pfrom)\n            )\n  )\n)",

advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ; remove disk from source peg\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?pfrom))\n      (not (top ?d ?pfrom))\n\n      ; place disk on top of disk ?t\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n      (top ?d ?pto)\n      (not (top ?t ?pto))\n\n      ; From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F.\nAs initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.\nMy goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.\nThe left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.\n\nMy plan is as follows:\n\n[PLAN]",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi_staged)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ; placement relations\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)       ; ?d is directly on peg ?p (no disk under it)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?under - disk) ; ?d is directly on top of disk ?under\n\n    ; top-of-peg: the disk currently at the top of a peg\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ; peg empty marker (true exactly when there are no disks on that peg)\n    (empty ?p - peg)\n\n    ; size ordering: smaller ?small ?big is true iff ?small is strictly smaller than ?big\n    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk)\n\n    ; staging / discrete time\n    (current-stage ?s - stage)\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move_from_peg_to_empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?pfrom)\n      (top ?d ?pfrom)\n      (empty ?pto)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ; remove disk from source peg\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?pfrom))\n      (not (top ?d ?pfrom))\n\n      ; place disk on destination peg as its top and as directly on-peg\n      (on-peg ?d ?pto)\n      (top ?d ?pto)\n\n      ; update emptiness of pegs\n      (empty ?pfrom)\n      (not (empty ?pto))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to a non-empty peg whose top is ?t (must be larger).\n  (:action move_from_peg_to_nonempty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg ?t - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?pfrom)\n      (top ?d ?pfrom)\n      (top ?t ?pto)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ; remove disk from source peg\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?pfrom))\n      (not (top ?d ?pfrom))\n\n      ; place disk on top of disk ?t\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n      (top ?d ?pto)\n      (not (top ?t ?pto))\n\n      ; source peg becomes empty (since disk was directly on peg and top)\n      (empty ?pfrom)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly on another disk (?under) to an empty peg.\n  (:action move_from_disk_to_empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?under)\n      (top ?d ?pfrom)\n      (empty ?pto)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ; remove disk from on top of ?under and from being top of source\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (not (top ?d ?pfrom))\n\n      ; place disk on destination peg as directly on-peg and top there\n      (on-peg ?d ?pto)\n      (top ?d ?pto)\n      (not (empty ?pto))\n\n      ; the disk under becomes the new top of the source peg\n      (top ?under ?pfrom)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly on another disk (?under) to a non-empty peg whose top is ?t (must be larger).\n  (:action move_from_disk_to_nonempty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?pfrom - peg ?pto - peg ?t - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?under)\n      (top ?d ?pfrom)\n      (top ?t ?pto)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ; remove disk from its previous placement and top of source\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (not (top ?d ?pfrom))\n\n      ; place disk on top of disk ?t\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n      (top ?d ?pto)\n      (not (top ?t ?pto))\n\n      ; the disk under becomes the new top of the source peg\n      (top ?under ?pfrom)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi_staged-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi_staged)\n\n  (:objects\n    ; disks smallest d1 ... largest d6\n    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 - disk\n\n    ; three pegs\n    peg-left peg-middle peg-right - peg\n\n    ; discrete stages: s0 .. s63 (2^6 - 1 = 63 moves required for optimal solution)\n    s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19 s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31\n    s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39 s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59 s60 s61 s62 s63 - stage\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ; initial stack on peg-middle: bottom d6 (directly on peg), then d5 on d6, d4 on d5, d3 on d4, d2 on d3, top d1 on d2\n    (on-peg d6 peg-middle)\n    (on-disk d5 d6)\n    (on-disk d4 d5)\n    (on-disk d3 d4)\n    (on-disk d2 d3)\n    (on-disk d1 d2)\n\n    ; top and emptiness facts for initial state\n    (top d1 peg-middle)\n    (empty peg-left)\n    (empty peg-right)\n\n    ; size ordering: d1 < d2 < ... < d6\n    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6)\n    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6)\n    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6)\n    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6)\n    (smaller d5 d6)\n\n    ; staging: start at s0\n    (current-stage s0)\n\n    ; successor relations for each adjacent stage (contiguous progression)\n    (next s0 s1) (next s1 s2) (next s2 s3) (next s3 s4) (next s4 s5) (next s5 s6) (next s6 s7) (next s7 s8) (next s8 s9) (next s9 s10)\n    (next s10 s11) (next s11 s12) (next s12 s13) (next s13 s14) (next s14 s15) (next s15 s16) (next s16 s17) (next s17 s18) (next s18 s19) (next s19 s20)\n    (next s20 s21) (next s21 s22) (next s22 s23) (next s23 s24) (next s24 s25) (next s25 s26) (next s26 s27) (next s27 s28) (next s28 s29) (next s29 s30)\n    (next s30 s31) (next s31 s32) (next s32 s33) (next s33 s34) (next s34 s35) (next s35 s36) (next s36 s37) (next s37 s38) (next s38 s39) (next s39 s40)\n    (next s40 s41) (next s41 s42) (next s42 s43) (next s43 s44) (next s44 s45) (next s45 s46) (next s46 s47) (next s47 s48) (next s48 s49) (next s49 s50)\n    (next s50 s51) (next s51 s52) (next s52 s53) (next s53 s54) (next s54 s55) (next s55 s56) (next s56 s57) (next s57 s58) (next s58 s59) (next s59 s60)\n    (next s60 s61) (next s61 s62) (next s62 s63)\n  )\n\n  (:goal (and\n    ; all six disks stacked on the right peg in correct order (d6 bottom ... d1 top)\n    (on-peg d6 peg-right)\n    (on-disk d5 d6)\n    (on-disk d4 d5)\n    (on-disk d3 d4)\n    (on-disk d2 d3)\n    (on-disk d1 d2)\n\n    ; top-of-peg fact for the final stack and emptiness requirements\n    (top d1 peg-right)\n    (empty peg-left)\n    (empty peg-middle)\n\n    ; require having reached final stage s63 (enforces exact number of stage-advancing moves)\n    (current-stage s63)\n  ))",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi_ordered)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types position stage disk peg)\n\n  ;; Treat disks and pegs as positions (they are declared as position-compatible\n  ;; by using them in predicates typed as 'position' below).\n  (:predicates\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - position)      ;; immediate supporting position: a peg or another disk\n    (top ?d - disk)                   ;; true iff no disk sits on ?d\n    (empty ?p - peg)                  ;; true iff no disk currently sits on the peg\n    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk) ;; size ordering relation: small < big\n    (current-stage ?s - stage)        ;; current discrete stage/timepoint\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)    ;; successor relation on stages\n  )\n\n  ;; Move when the disk to move is directly on a peg and the peg becomes empty after move.\n  (:action move-from-peg-only-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)            ;; disk is directly on the peg (so it is the only disk whose support is this peg)\n      (top ?d)                 ;; disk has nothing on top of it (is movable)\n      (empty ?to)              ;; destination peg is empty\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; stage progression\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; move the disk from the source peg to the destination peg\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates: source peg becomes empty, destination peg becomes non-empty\n      (empty ?from)\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; top status: moving a top disk preserves it being top after the move (no change required)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move when the disk to move is directly on a peg and the destination peg has a top disk.\n  (:action move-from-peg-only-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)            ;; disk is directly on source peg\n      (top ?d)\n      (top ?t)                 ;; t is the top disk on destination peg\n      (on ?t ?to)              ;; t sits on destination peg (so destination peg non-empty)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)          ;; size constraint: cannot place larger on smaller\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; stage progression\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; update top facts: t is no longer top, d becomes top\n      (not (top ?t))\n      (top ?d)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes empty (d was directly on the peg)\n      (empty ?from)\n\n      ;; destination peg remains non-empty (no explicit change needed other than top updates)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move when the disk to move is on top of another disk (i.e., its support is a disk),\n  ;; and the destination peg is empty.\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)           ;; d sits on another disk\n      (top ?d)                 ;; d has nothing on top\n      (empty ?to)              ;; destination peg is empty\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; stage progression\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate d from being on a disk to being on peg\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; the disk that was under becomes top (d removed)\n      (top ?under)\n\n      ;; destination peg becomes non-empty\n      (not (empty ?to))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move when the disk to move is on top of another disk and the destination peg has a top disk.\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)           ;; d sits on under\n      (top ?d)\n      (top ?t)                 ;; t is top disk on destination peg\n      (on ?t ?to)              ;; t sits on destination peg\n      (smaller ?d ?t)          ;; size ordering\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; stage progression\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate d to sit on t\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; update top facts: under becomes top, t is no longer top, d becomes top\n      (top ?under)\n      (not (top ?t))\n      (top ?d)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi_ordered)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg - object stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on ?d - disk ?x - object)      ; disk ?d is directly on object ?x (disk or peg)\n    (top ?d - disk)                 ; ?d has no disk on top\n    (empty ?p - peg)                ; peg has no disks\n    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk) ;; size ordering: small < big\n    (current-stage ?s - stage)      ; current time/stage\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)  ; successor relation for stages\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-from-peg-to-empty-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)    ;; disk is directly supported by source peg\n      (top ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes empty; destination peg becomes non-empty\n      (empty ?from)\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; top facts: ?d remains top (it was top before and is top on destination)\n      (top ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto another top disk on some peg.\n  (:action move-from-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)    ;; disk is directly on source peg\n      (top ?d)\n      (top ?t)         ;; destination top disk\n      (on ?t ?to)      ;; that top disk sits on destination peg\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; Update tops: destination top no longer top, moved disk becomes top\n      (not (top ?t))\n      (top ?d)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes empty (disk was directly on the peg)\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-empty-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)     ;; d sits on another disk\n      (top ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; the disk that was under becomes top\n      (top ?under)\n\n      ;; destination peg becomes non-empty\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk becomes top at destination\n      (top ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto another top disk.\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)\n      (top ?d)\n      (top ?t)\n      (on ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; update top facts\n      (top ?under)\n      (not (top ?t))\n      (top ?d)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi_ordered-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi_ordered)\n\n  (:objects\n    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 - disk\n    peg-left peg-middle peg-right - peg\n    s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19 s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31\n    s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39 s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59 s60 s61 s62 s63 - stage\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; middle implicitly non-empty (no empty fact)\n    (empty peg-left)\n    (empty peg-right)\n\n    ;; Size ordering\n    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6)\n    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6)\n    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6)\n    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6)\n    (smaller d5 d6)\n\n    ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi_ordered)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage - object)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on ?d - disk ?x - object)       ; disk ?d is directly on object ?x (disk or peg)\n    (clear ?x - object)             ; object (disk or peg) has nothing on top\n    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk) ; size ordering: small < big\n    (current-stage ?s - stage)      ; current time/stage\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)  ; successor relation for stages\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source becomes clear; destination no longer clear; moved disk is clear (top)\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto the top disk of another peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?toPeg - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)        ;; disk is directly on source peg\n      (clear ?d)           ;; top disk\n      (on ?t ?toPeg)       ;; destination top disk sits on destination peg\n      (clear ?t)           ;; destination top disk is clear (no disk above)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)      ;; size ordering\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; source becomes clear; destination top disk no longer clear; moved disk is clear (top)\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?t))\n      (clear ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; update clears: under becomes clear, destination top no longer clear, moved disk is clear\n      (clear ?under)\n      (not (clear ?t))\n      (clear ?d)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi_ordered)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; direct support relations: a disk directly on a peg or directly on another disk\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?under - disk)\n\n    ;; top/clear status separate for disks and pegs\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; size ordering\n    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk)\n\n    ;; explicit discrete stage progression\n    (current-stage ?s - stage)\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from source peg, put on destination peg\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes clear (disk was top and directly on peg)\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ;; destination peg now has a top disk\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto the top disk of another peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)   ;; disk is directly on source peg\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its peg\n      (clear-disk ?t)     ;; destination disk is top (on some peg or disk)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)     ;; size ordering\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from source peg, put on top of disk ?t\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes clear\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ;; destination top disk now has a disk above it\n      (not (clear-disk ?t))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?under) ;; disk is directly on another disk\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its stack\n      (clear-peg ?to)     ;; destination peg empty\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from its under-disk, place on peg\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; the disk that was under becomes top/clear\n      (clear-disk ?under)\n\n      ;; destination peg now occupied on top\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto another top disk.\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?t - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?under) ;; disk directly on another disk\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its stack\n      (clear-disk ?t)     ;; destination disk is top\n      (smaller ?d ?t)     ;; size ordering\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk onto destination disk\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; the disk that was under becomes clear\n      (clear-disk ?under)\n\n      ;; destination disk no longer clear (has disk on top)\n      (not (clear-disk ?t))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi_ordered)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; direct support relations: a disk directly on a peg or directly on another disk\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?under - disk)\n\n    ;; top/clear status separate for disks and pegs\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; size ordering (small -> big)\n    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk)\n\n    ;; explicit discrete stage progression\n    (current-stage ?s - stage)\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from source peg, put on destination peg\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes empty (was occupied only by this top-on-peg disk)\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ;; destination peg now occupied on top\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto the top disk of another peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)   ;; disk is directly on source peg\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its peg\n      (clear-disk ?t)     ;; destination disk is top\n      (smaller ?d ?t)     ;; size ordering: ?d smaller than ?t\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from source peg, put on top of disk ?t\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes empty\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ;; destination top disk no longer clear (has a disk on it)\n      (not (clear-disk ?t))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?under) ;; disk is directly on another disk\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its stack\n      (clear-peg ?to)     ;; destination peg empty\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from its under-disk, place on peg\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; the disk that was under becomes top/clear\n      (clear-disk ?under)\n\n      ;; destination peg now occupied on top\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto another top disk.\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?t - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?under) ;; disk directly on another disk\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its stack\n      (clear-disk ?t)     ;; destination disk is top\n      (smaller ?d ?t)     ;; size ordering: ?d smaller than ?t\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk onto destination disk\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; the disk that was under becomes clear (now top)\n      (clear-disk ?under)\n\n      ;; destination disk no longer clear (has disk on top)\n      (not (clear-disk ?t))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi_ordered-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi_ordered)\n\n  (:objects\n    diskA diskB diskC diskD diskE diskF - disk\n    peg-left peg-middle peg-right - peg\n    s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19 s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31\n    s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39 s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59 s60 s61 s62 s63 - stage\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; final clears: left and middle pegs empty; top disk clear\n    (clear-peg peg-left)\n    (clear-peg peg-middle)\n    (clear-disk diskA)\n\n    ;; Require exact terminal stage after 63 moves (2^6 - 1)\n    (current-stage s63)\n  ))\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi_ordered)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; direct support relations: a disk directly on a peg or directly on another disk\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?under - disk)\n\n    ;; top/clear status separate for disks and pegs\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; size ordering (small -> big)\n    (smaller ?small - disk ?big - disk)\n\n    ;; explicit discrete stage progression\n    (current-stage ?s - stage)\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from source peg, put on destination peg\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes empty (preconditions ensure this peg had only this disk)\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ;; destination peg now occupied on top\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto the top disk of another peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)   ;; disk is directly on source peg (bottom support)\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its peg (no disk above)\n      (clear-disk ?t)     ;; destination disk is top\n      (smaller ?d ?t)     ;; size ordering: ?d smaller than ?t\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from source peg, put on top of disk ?t\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes empty (preconditions ensure this peg had only this disk)\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ;; destination top disk no longer clear (has a disk on it)\n      (not (clear-disk ?t))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?under) ;; disk is directly on another disk\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its stack\n      (clear-peg ?to)     ;; destination peg empty\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk: remove from its under-disk, place on peg\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; the disk that was under becomes top/clear\n      (clear-disk ?under)\n\n      ;; destination peg now occupied on top\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, onto another top disk.\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?t - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?under) ;; disk directly on another disk\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ;; disk is top of its stack\n      (clear-disk ?t)     ;; destination disk is top\n      (smaller ?d ?t)     ;; size ordering: ?d smaller than ?t\n      (current-stage ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current-stage ?s))\n      (current-stage ?s2)\n\n      ;; relocate disk onto destination disk\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; the disk that was under becomes clear (now top)\n      (clear-disk ?under)\n\n      ;; destination disk no longer clear (has disk on top)\n      (not (clear-disk ?t))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi_ordered-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi_ordered)\n\n  (:objects\n    diskA diskB diskC diskD diskE diskF - disk\n    peg-left peg-middle peg-right - peg\n    s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19 s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31\n    s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39 s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59 s60 s61 s62 s63 - stage\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; - Total moves: 63 (minimal for 6 disks: 2^6 - 1).
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 6 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.
The left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 6 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.
The left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi-6)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types obj)

  (:predicates
    ;; classification predicates (explicit, used as hard constraints)
    (disk ?x - obj)
    (peg ?x - obj)
    (step ?s - obj)

    ;; structural predicates
    ;; a disk ?d is directly on support ?p (where ?p is either a peg or another disk)
    (on ?d - obj ?p - obj)

    ;; true iff nothing is on top of this place (place may be a peg or a disk)
    (clear ?x - obj)

    ;; size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b
    (smaller ?a - obj ?b - obj)

    ;; step sequencing control
    (at-step ?s - obj)
    (succ ?s - obj ?s2 - obj)
  )

  ;; Move a top disk onto a peg (peg must be clear). Enforces single-disk move,
  ;; top-only source, destination clear, and strict step ordering.
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - obj ?from - obj ?to - obj ?s - obj ?snext - obj)
    :precondition (and
      (disk ?d)
      (at-step ?s)
      (succ ?s ?snext)

      ;; disk must be currently directly on ?from (either peg or disk)
      (on ?d ?from)

      ;; only top disks may be moved
      (clear ?d)

      ;; destination must be a peg and must be clear (top position)
      (peg ?to)
      (clear ?to)

      ;; forbid null/no-op moves
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; relocate the disk
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; update clearness: the former support becomes clear, the destination is no longer clear
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?to))

      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs at each step
      (not (at-step ?s))
      (at-step ?snext)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk onto another disk. Enforces smaller-on-larger rule,
  ;; top-only source, destination clear, single-disk move, and step ordering.
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - obj ?from - obj ?to - obj ?s - obj ?snext - obj)
    :precondition (and
      (disk ?d)
      (disk ?to)
      (at-step ?s)
      (succ ?s ?snext)

      ;; disk must be currently directly on ?from (either peg or disk)
      (on ?d ?from)

      ;; only top disks may be moved
      (clear ?d)

      ;; destination disk must be top (clear)
      (clear ?to)

      ;; size constraint: moving disk must be strictly smaller than destination disk
      (smaller ?d ?to)

      ;; forbid null/no-op moves
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; relocate the disk
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; update clearness: the former support becomes clear, the destination is no longer clear
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?to))

      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs at each step
      (not (at-step ?s))
      (at-step ?snext)
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi6-instance)
  (:domain hanoi-6)

  ;; Objects: disks d1..d6 (d1 smallest, d6 largest), pegs p1 p2 p3, steps s0..s63
  (:objects
     d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 - obj
     p1 p2 p3 - obj
     s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19
     s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31 s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39
     s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59
     s60 s61 s62 s63 - obj
  )

  (:init
    ;; classification facts
    (disk d1) (disk d2) (disk d3) (disk d4) (disk d5) (disk d6)
    (peg p1) (peg p2) (peg p3)
    (step s0) (step s1) (step s2) (step s3) (step s4) (step s5) (step s6) (step s7) (step s8) (step s9)
    (step s10) (step s11) (step s12) (step s13) (step s14) (step s15) (step s16) (step s17) (step s18) (step s19)
    (step s20) (step s21) (step s22) (step s23) (step s24) (step s25) (step s26) (step s27) (step s28) (step s29)
    (step s30) (step s31) (step s32) (step s33) (step s34) (step s35) (step s36) (step s37) (step s38) (step s39)
    (step s40) (step s41) (step s42) (step s43) (step s44) (step s45) (step s46) (step s47) (step s48) (step s49)
    (step s50) (step s51) (step s52) (step s53) (step s54) (step s55) (step s56) (step s57) (step s58) (step s59)
    (step s60) (step s61) (step s62) (step s63)

    ;; successor (step) chain enforces move ordering and contiguity: s0->s1->...->s63
    (succ s0 s1) (succ s1 s2) (succ s2 s3) (succ s3 s4) (succ s4 s5) (succ s5 s6) (succ s6 s7) (succ s7 s8) (succ s8 s9) (succ s9 s10)
    (succ s10 s11) (succ s11 s12) (succ s12 s13) (succ s13 s14) (succ s14 s15) (succ s15 s16) (succ s16 s17) (succ s17 s18) (succ s18 s19) (succ s19 s20)
    (succ s20 s21) (succ s21 s22) (succ s22 s23) (succ s23 s24) (succ s24 s25) (succ s25 s26) (succ s26 s27) (succ s27 s28) (succ s28 s29) (succ s29 s30)
    (succ s30 s31) (succ s31 s32) (succ s32 s33) (succ s33 s34) (succ s34 s35) (succ s35 s36) (succ s36 s37) (succ s37 s38) (succ s38 s39) (succ s39 s40)
    (succ s40 s41) (succ s41 s42) (succ s42 s43) (succ s43 s44) (succ s44 s45) (succ s45 s46) (succ s46 s47) (succ s47 s48) (succ s48 s49) (succ s49 s50)
    (succ s50 s51) (succ s51 s52) (succ s52 s53) (succ s53 s54) (succ s54 s55) (succ s55 s56) (succ s56 s57) (succ s57 s58) (succ s58 s59) (succ s59 s60)
    (succ s60 s61) (succ s61 s62) (succ s62 s63)

    ;; initial step token: exactly one step active -> enforces one action per step
    (at-step s0)

    ;; initial stacking on peg p1 (largest d6 at bottom, smallest d1 at top)
    (on d6 p1)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)

    ;; top-of-stack and clear facts
    (clear d1)    ;; only the smallest disk at top is clear initially
    (clear p2) (clear p3)  ;; empty pegs are clear

    ;; size ordering: smaller relations for all i<j (explicit, used as hard constraints)
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6)
    (smaller d5 d6)
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ;; final tower must be on peg p3 with same ordering d6 bottom -> d1 top
      (on d6 p3)
      (on d5 d6)
      (on d4 d5)
      (on d3 d4)
      (on d2 d3)
      (on d1 d2)

      ;; final step token: require exactly 63 moves have occurred (s63 is reached)
      (at-step s63)
    )
  )
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi-6)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types obj)

  (:predicates
    ;; classification predicates (explicit, used as hard constraints)
    (disk ?x - obj)
    (peg ?x - obj)
    (step ?s - obj)

    ;; structural predicates
    ;; a disk ?d is directly on support ?p (where ?p is either a peg or another disk)
    (on ?d - obj ?p - obj)

    ;; true iff nothing is on top of this place (place may be a peg or a disk)
    (clear ?x - obj)

    ;; size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b
    (smaller ?a - obj ?b - obj)

    ;; step sequencing control
    (at-step ?s - obj)
    (succ ?s - obj ?s2 - obj)
  )

  ;; Move a top disk onto a peg (peg must be clear). Enforces single-disk move,
  ;; top-only source, destination clear, and strict step ordering.
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - obj ?from - obj ?to - obj ?s - obj ?snext - obj)
    :precondition (and
      (disk ?d)
      (at-step ?s)
      (succ ?s ?snext)

      ;; disk must be currently directly on ?from (either peg or disk)
      (on ?d ?from)

      ;; only top disks may be moved
      (clear ?d)

      ;; destination must be a peg and must be clear (top position)
      (peg ?to)
      (clear ?to)

      ;; forbid null/no-op moves
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; relocate the disk
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; update clearness: the former support becomes clear, the destination is no longer clear
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?to))

      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs at each step
      (not (at-step ?s))
      (at-step ?snext)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk onto another disk. Enforces smaller-on-larger rule,
  ;; top-only source, destination clear, single-disk move, and step ordering.
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - obj ?from - obj ?to - obj ?s - obj ?snext - obj)
    :precondition (and
      (disk ?d)
      (disk ?to)
      (at-step ?s)
      (succ ?s ?snext)

      ;; disk must be currently directly on ?from (either peg or disk)
      (on ?d ?from)

      ;; only top disks may be moved
      (clear ?d)

      ;; destination disk must be top (clear)
      (clear ?to)

      ;; size constraint: moving disk must be strictly smaller than destination disk
      (smaller ?d ?to)

      ;; forbid null/no-op moves
      (not (= ?from ?to))
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; relocate the disk
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; update clearness: the former support becomes clear, the destination is no longer clear
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?to))

      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs at each step
      (not (at-step ?s))
      (at-step ?snext)
    )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi6-instance)
  (:domain hanoi-6)

  ;; Objects: disks d1..d6 (d1 smallest, d6 largest), pegs p1 p2 p3, steps s0..s63
  (:objects
     d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 - obj
     p1 p2 p3 - obj
     s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19
     s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31 s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39
     s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59
     s60 s61 s62 s63 - obj
  )

  (:init
    ;; classification facts
    (disk d1) (disk d2) (disk d3) (disk d4) (disk d5) (disk d6)
    (peg p1) (peg p2) (peg p3)
    (step s0) (step s1) (step s2) (step s3) (step s4) (step s5) (step s6) (step s7) (step s8) (step s9)
    (step s10) (step s11) (step s12) (step s13) (step s14) (step s15) (step s16) (step s17) (step s18) (step s19)
    (step s20) (step s21) (step s22) (step s23) (step s24) (step s25) (step s26) (step s27) (step s28) (step s29)
    (step s30) (step s31) (step s32) (step s33) (step s34) (step s35) (step s36) (step s37) (step s38) (step s39)
    (step s40) (step s41) (step s42) (step s43) (step s44) (step s45) (step s46) (step s47) (step s48) (step s49)
    (step s50) (step s51) (step s52) (step s53) (step s54) (step s55) (step s56) (step s57) (step s58) (step s59)
    (step s60) (step s61) (step s62) (step s63)

    ;; successor (step) chain enforces move ordering and contiguity: s0->s1->...->s63
    (succ s0 s1) (succ s1 s2) (succ s2 s3) (succ s3 s4) (succ s4 s5) (succ s5 s6) (succ s6 s7) (succ s7 s8) (succ s8 s9) (succ s9 s10)
    (succ s10 s11) (succ s11 s12) (succ s12 s13) (succ s13 s14) (succ s14 s15) (succ s15 s16) (succ s16 s17) (succ s17 s18) (succ s18 s19) (succ s19 s20)
    (succ s20 s21) (succ s21 s22) (succ s22 s23) (succ s23 s24) (succ s24 s25) (succ s25 s26) (succ s26 s27) (succ s27 s28) (succ s28 s29) (succ s29 s30)
    (succ s30 s31) (succ s31 s32) (succ s32 s33) (succ s33 s34) (succ s34 s35) (succ s35 s36) (succ s36 s37) (succ s37 s38) (succ s38 s39) (succ s39 s40)
    (succ s40 s41) (succ s41 s42) (succ s42 s43) (succ s43 s44) (succ s44 s45) (succ s45 s46) (succ s46 s47) (succ s47 s48) (succ s48 s49) (succ s49 s50)
    (succ s50 s51) (succ s51 s52) (succ s52 s53) (succ s53 s54) (succ s54 s55) (succ s55 s56) (succ s56 s57) (succ s57 s58) (succ s58 s59) (succ s59 s60)
    (succ s60 s61) (succ s61 s62) (succ s62 s63)

    ;; initial step token: exactly one step active -> enforces one action per step
    (at-step s0)

    ;; initial stacking on peg p1 (largest d6 at bottom, smallest d1 at top)
    (on d6 p1)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)

    ;; top-of-stack and clear facts
    (clear d1)    ;; only the smallest disk at top is clear initially
    (clear p2) (clear p3)  ;; empty pegs are clear

    ;; size ordering: smaller relations for all i<j (explicit, used as hard constraints)
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6)
    (smaller d5 d6)
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ;; final tower must be on peg p3 with same ordering d6 bottom -> d1 top
      (on d6 p3)
      (on d5 d6)
      (on d4 d5)
      (on d3 d4)
      (on d2 d3)
      (on d1 d2)

      ;; final step token: require exactly 63 moves have occurred (s63 is reached)
      (at-step s63)
    )
  )
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types obj)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; classification predicates (explicit, used as hard constraints)\n    (disk ?x - obj)\n    (peg ?x - obj)\n    (step ?s - obj)\n\n    ;; structural predicates\n    ;; a disk ?d is directly on support ?p (where ?p is either a peg or another disk)\n    (on ?d - obj ?p - obj)\n\n    ;; true iff nothing is on top of this place (place may be a peg or a disk)\n    (clear ?x - obj)\n\n    ;; size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b\n    (smaller ?a - obj ?b - obj)\n\n    ;; step sequencing control\n    (at-step ?s - obj)\n    (succ ?s - obj ?s2 - obj)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto a peg (peg must be clear). Enforces single-disk move,\n  ;; top-only source, destination clear, and strict step ordering.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - obj ?from - obj ?to - obj ?s - obj ?snext - obj)\n    :precondition (and\n      (disk ?d)\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk must be currently directly on ?from (either peg or disk)\n      (on ?d ?from)\n\n      ;; only top disks may be moved\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination must be a peg and must be clear (top position)\n      (peg ?to)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid null/no-op moves\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; update clearness: the former support becomes clear, the destination is no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs at each step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto another disk. Enforces smaller-on-larger rule,\n  ;; top-only source, destination clear, single-disk move, and step ordering.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - obj ?from - obj ?to - obj ?s - obj ?snext - obj)\n    :precondition (and\n      (disk ?d)\n      (disk ?to)\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk must be currently directly on ?from (either peg or disk)\n      (on ?d ?from)\n\n      ;; only top disks may be moved\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination disk must be top (clear)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; size constraint: moving disk must be strictly smaller than destination disk\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid null/no-op moves\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; update clearness: the former support becomes clear, the destination is no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs at each step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi6-instance)\n  (:domain hanoi-6)\n\n  ;; Objects: disks d1..d6 (d1 smallest, d6 largest), pegs p1 p2 p3, steps s0..s63\n  (:objects\n     d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 - obj\n     p1 p2 p3 - obj\n     s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19\n     s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31 s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39\n     s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59\n     s60 s61 s62 s63 - obj\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; classification facts\n    (disk d1) (disk d2) (disk d3) (disk d4) (disk d5) (disk d6)\n    (peg p1) (peg p2) (peg p3)\n    (step s0) (step s1) (step s2) (step s3) (step s4) (step s5) (step s6) (step s7) (step s8) (step s9)\n    (step s10) (step s11) (step s12) (step s13) (step s14) (step s15) (step s16) (step s17) (step s18) (step s19)\n    (step s20) (step s21) (step s22) (step s23) (step s24) (step s25) (step s26) (step s27) (step s28) (step s29)\n    (step s30) (step s31) (step s32) (step s33) (step s34) (step s35) (step s36) (step s37) (step s38) (step s39)\n    (step s40) (step s41) (step s42) (step s43) (step s44) (step s45) (step s46) (step s47) (step s48) (step s49)\n    (step s50) (step s51) (step s52) (step s53) (step s54) (step s55) (step s56) (step s57) (step s58) (step s59)\n    (step s60) (step s61) (step s62) (step s63)\n\n    ;; successor (step) chain enforces move ordering and contiguity: s0->s1->...->s63\n    (succ s0 s1) (succ s1 s2) (succ s2 s3) (succ s3 s4) (succ s4 s5) (succ s5 s6) (succ s6 s7) (succ s7 s8) (succ s8 s9) (succ s9 s10)\n    (succ s10 s11) (succ s11 s12) (succ s12 s13) (succ s13 s14) (succ s14 s15) (succ s15 s16) (succ s16 s17) (succ s17 s18) (succ s18 s19) (succ s19 s20)\n    (succ s20 s21) (succ s21 s22) (succ s22 s23) (succ s23 s24) (succ s24 s25) (succ s25 s26) (succ s26 s27) (succ s27 s28) (succ s28 s29) (succ s29 s30)\n    (succ s30 s31) (succ s31 s32) (succ s32 s33) (succ s33 s34) (succ s34 s35) (succ s35 s36) (succ s36 s37) (succ s37 s38) (succ s38 s39) (succ s39 s40)\n    (succ s40 s41) (succ s41 s42) (succ s42 s43) (succ s43 s44) (succ s44 s45) (succ s45 s46) (succ s46 s47) (succ s47 s48) (succ s48 s49) (succ s49 s50)\n    (succ s50 s51) (succ s51 s52) (succ s52 s53) (succ s53 s54) (succ s54 s55) (succ s55 s56) (succ s56 s57) (succ s57 s58) (succ s58 s59) (succ s59 s60)\n    (succ s60 s61) (succ s61 s62) (succ s62 s63)\n\n    ;; initial step token: exactly one step active -> enforces one action per step\n    (at-step s0)\n\n    ;; initial stacking on peg p1 (largest d6 at bottom, smallest d1 at top)\n    (on d6 p1)\n    (on d5 d6)\n    (on d4 d5)\n    (on d3 d4)\n    (on d2 d3)\n    (on d1 d2)\n\n    ;; top-of-stack and clear facts\n    (clear d1)    ;; only the smallest disk at top is clear initially\n    (clear p2) (clear p3)  ;; empty pegs are clear\n\n    ;; size ordering: smaller relations for all i<j (explicit, used as hard constraints)\n    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6)\n    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6)\n    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6)\n    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6)\n    (smaller d5 d6)\n  )\n\n  (:goal\n    (and\n      ;; final tower must be on peg p3 with same ordering d6 bottom -> d1 top\n      (on d6 p3)\n      (on d5 d6)\n      (on d4 d5)\n      (on d3 d4)\n      (on d2 d3)\n      (on d1 d2)\n\n      ;; final step token: require exactly 63 moves have occurred (s63 is reached)\n      (at-step s63)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "target_solver": "FastDownwards",
