    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types place step - obj\n          disk peg - place)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; classification predicates (explicit, used as hard constraints)\n    (disk ?x - disk)\n    (peg ?x - peg)\n\n    ;; structural predicates\n    ;; a disk ?d is directly on support ?p (where ?p is either a peg or another disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n\n    ;; true iff nothing is on top of this place (place may be a peg or a disk)\n    (clear ?x - place)\n\n    ;; size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b\n    (smaller ?a - disk ?b - disk)\n\n    ;; step sequencing control\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    (succ ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto an empty peg (peg must be clear). Enforces single-disk move,\n  ;; top-only source, destination clear, and strict step ordering.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk must be currently directly on ?from (either peg or disk)\n      (on ?d ?from)\n\n      ;; only top disks may be moved\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination must be a peg and must be clear (top position)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid null/no-op moves (prevents from=to when both are pegs)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; update clearness: the former support becomes clear (its top was removed),\n      ;; the destination is no longer clear (it now has a disk on top)\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs at each step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk onto another disk. Enforces smaller-on-larger rule,\n  ;; top-only source, destination clear, single-disk move, and step ordering.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk must be currently directly on ?from (either peg or disk)\n      (on ?d ?from)\n\n      ;; only top disks may be moved\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination disk must be top (clear)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; size constraint: moving disk must be strictly smaller than destination disk\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid null/no-op moves\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; update clearness: the former support becomes clear, the destination is no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs at each step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n)",

initial step token: exactly one step active -> enforces one action per step\n    (at-step s0)\n\n    ;; initial stacking on peg p1 (largest d6 at bottom, smallest d1 at top)\n    ;; on is direct-support: on d6 p1 means d6 directly on peg p1; on d5 d6 means d5 directly on d6, ...\n    (on d6 p1)\n    (on d5 d6)\n    (on d4 d5)\n    (on d3 d4)\n    (on d2 d3)\n    (on d1 d2)\n\n    ;; top-of-stack and clear facts\n    (clear d1)    ;; only the smallest disk at top is clear initially\n    (clear p2) (clear p3)  ;; empty pegs are clear\n\n    ;; size ordering: smaller relations for all i<j (explicit, used as hard constraints)\n    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6)\n    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6)\n    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6)\n    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6)\n    (smaller d5 d6)\n  )\n\n  (:goal\n    (and\n      ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    place step - object\n    disk peg - place\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n\n    ;; true iff nothing is directly on top of this place (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b\n    (smaller ?a - disk ?b - disk)\n\n    ;; step sequencing control\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    (succ ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto an empty peg.\n  ;; Enforce explicit stage progression and forbid no-op moves (from == to).\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination peg must be clear (no disk directly on it)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; explicit inequality to prevent vacuous moves\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n      (not (= ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto another disk (must be larger and top).\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination disk must be top (clear) and strictly larger\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; explicit inequalities to avoid degenerate/no-op moves\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n      (not (= ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n)",

initial active step\n    (at-step s0)\n\n    ;; initial stacking: middle peg holds, top-to-bottom: dA (smallest) ... dF (largest)\n    (on dA dB)\n    (on dB dC)\n    (on dC dD)\n    (on dD dE)\n    (on dE dF)\n    (on dF peg_mid)\n\n    ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    place step - object\n    disk peg - place\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n\n    ;; true iff nothing is directly on top of this place (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b\n    (smaller ?a - disk ?b - disk)\n\n    ;; step sequencing control\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    (succ ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto an empty peg.\n  ;; Enforce explicit stage progression and forbid vacuous moves by requiring the disk is not already on the destination.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination peg must be clear (no disk directly on it)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; disk must not already be on the destination (prevents vacuous from==to moves without equality usage)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto another disk (must be larger and top).\n  ;; Forbid vacuous moves by ensuring the disk is not already on the destination.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination disk must be top (clear) and strictly larger\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; disk must not already be on the destination (prevents vacuous from==to moves without equality usage)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi6-instance)\n  (:domain hanoi-6)\n\n  ;; Objects: disks dA..dF (dA smallest, dF largest), pegs peg_left peg_mid peg_right, steps s0..s63\n  (:objects\n     dA dB dC dD dE dF - disk\n     peg_left peg_mid peg_right - peg\n     s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19\n     s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31 s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39\n     s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59\n     s60 s61 s62 s63 - step\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; successor chain s0->s1->...->s63\n    (succ s0 s1) (succ s1 s2) (succ s2 s3) (succ s3 s4) (succ s4 s5) (succ s5 s6) (succ s6 s7) (succ s7 s8) (succ s8 s9) (succ s9 s10)\n    (succ s10 s11) (succ s11 s12) (succ s12 s13) (succ s13 s14) (succ s14 s15) (succ s15 s16) (succ s16 s17) (succ s17 s18) (succ s18 s19) (succ s19 s20)\n    (succ s20 s21) (succ s21 s22) (succ s22 s23) (succ s23 s24) (succ s24 s25) (succ s25 s26) (succ s26 s27) (succ s27 s28) (succ s28 s29) (succ s29 s30)\n    (succ s30 s31) (succ s31 s32) (succ s32 s33) (succ s33 s34) (succ s34 s35) (succ s35 s36) (succ s36 s37) (succ s37 s38) (succ s38 s39) (succ s39 s40)\n    (succ s40 s41) (succ s41 s42) (succ s42 s43) (succ s43 s44) (succ s44 s45) (succ s45 s46) (succ s46 s47) (succ s47 s48) (succ s48 s49) (succ s49 s50)\n    (succ s50 s51) (succ s51 s52) (succ s52 s53) (succ s53 s54) (succ s54 s55) (succ s55 s56) (succ s56 s57) (succ s57 s58) (succ s58 s59) (succ s59 s60)\n    (succ s60 s61) (succ s61 s62) (succ s62 s63)\n\n    ;; initial active step\n    (at-step s0)\n\n    ;; initial stacking: middle peg holds, top-to-bottom: dA (smallest) ... dF (largest)\n    (on dA dB)\n    (on dB dC)\n    (on dC dD)\n    (on dD dE)\n    (on dE dF)\n    (on dF peg_mid)\n\n    ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    place step - object\n    disk peg - place\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n\n    ;; true iff nothing is directly on top of this place (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b\n    (smaller ?a - disk ?b - disk)\n\n    ;; step sequencing control: exactly one action consumes the current step token and produces its successor\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    (succ ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto an empty peg.\n  ;; Requires the moved disk to be top (clear) and advances the explicit step token.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination peg must be empty (no disk directly on it)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid vacuous moves (prevents from==to or moving to current support)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto another disk (must be larger and top).\n  ;; Requires the target disk to be the top disk and strictly larger; advances the explicit step token.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination disk must be top (clear) and strictly larger\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid vacuous moves (prevents from==to or moving to same support)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n)",

initial active step\n    (at-step s0)\n\n    ;; initial stacking: middle peg holds, top-to-bottom: da (smallest) ... df (largest)\n    (on da db)\n    (on db dc)\n    (on dc dd)\n    (on dd de)\n    (on de df)\n    (on df peg_mid)\n\n    ;; initial clearness: top disk da is clear, empty pegs (left and right) are clear\n    (clear da)\n    (clear peg_left) (clear peg_right)\n\n    ;; static size ordering (transitively enumerated): all i<j pairs smaller relation\n    (smaller da db) (smaller da dc) (smaller da dd) (smaller da de) (smaller da df)\n    (smaller db dc) (smaller db dd) (smaller db de) (smaller db df)\n    (smaller dc dd) (smaller dc de) (smaller dc df)\n    (smaller dd de) (smaller dd df)\n    (smaller de df)\n  )\n\n  (:goal\n    (and\n      ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    place step - object\n    disk peg - place\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n\n    ;; true iff nothing is directly on top of this place (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b\n    (smaller ?a - disk ?b - disk)\n\n    ;; step sequencing control: exactly one action consumes the current step token and produces its successor\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    (succ ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto an empty peg.\n  ;; Requires the moved disk to be top (clear) and advances the explicit step token.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination peg must be empty (no disk directly on it)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid vacuous moves (prevents from==to or moving to current support)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto another disk (must be larger and top).\n  ;; Requires the target disk to be the top disk and strictly larger; advances the explicit step token.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination disk must be top (clear) and strictly larger\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid vacuous moves (prevents from==to or moving to same support)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi6-instance)\n  (:domain hanoi-6)\n\n  ;; Objects: disks da..df (da smallest, df largest), pegs peg_left peg_mid peg_right, steps s0..s63\n  (:objects\n     da db dc dd de df - disk\n     peg_left peg_mid peg_right - peg\n     s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19\n     s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31 s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39\n     s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59\n     s60 s61 s62 s63 - step\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; successor chain s0->s1->...->s63 (explicit ordered stages; exactly one action consumes each stage)\n    (succ s0 s1) (succ s1 s2) (succ s2 s3) (succ s3 s4) (succ s4 s5) (succ s5 s6) (succ s6 s7) (succ s7 s8) (succ s8 s9) (succ s9 s10)\n    (succ s10 s11) (succ s11 s12) (succ s12 s13) (succ s13 s14) (succ s14 s15) (succ s15 s16) (succ s16 s17) (succ s17 s18) (succ s18 s19) (succ s19 s20)\n    (succ s20 s21) (succ s21 s22) (succ s22 s23) (succ s23 s24) (succ s24 s25) (succ s25 s26) (succ s26 s27) (succ s27 s28) (succ s28 s29) (succ s29 s30)\n    (succ s30 s31) (succ s31 s32) (succ s32 s33) (succ s33 s34) (succ s34 s35) (succ s35 s36) (succ s36 s37) (succ s37 s38) (succ s38 s39) (succ s39 s40)\n    (succ s40 s41) (succ s41 s42) (succ s42 s43) (succ s43 s44) (succ s44 s45) (succ s45 s46) (succ s46 s47) (succ s47 s48) (succ s48 s49) (succ s49 s50)\n    (succ s50 s51) (succ s51 s52) (succ s52 s53) (succ s53 s54) (succ s54 s55) (succ s55 s56) (succ s56 s57) (succ s57 s58) (succ s58 s59) (succ s59 s60)\n    (succ s60 s61) (succ s61 s62) (succ s62 s63)\n\n    ;; initial active step\n    (at-step s0)\n\n    ;; initial stacking: middle peg holds, top-to-bottom: da (smallest) ... df (largest)\n    (on da db)\n    (on db dc)\n    (on dc dd)\n    (on dd de)\n    (on de df)\n    (on df peg_mid)\n\n    ;; initial clearness: top disk da is clear, empty pegs (left and right) are clear\n    (clear da)\n    (clear peg_left) (clear peg_right)\n\n    ;; static size ordering (transitively enumerated): all i<j pairs smaller relation\n    (smaller da db) (smaller da dc) (smaller da dd) (smaller da de) (smaller da df)\n    (smaller db dc) (smaller db dd) (smaller db de) (smaller db df)\n    (smaller dc dd) (smaller dc de) (smaller dc df)\n    (smaller dd de) (smaller dd df)\n    (smaller de df)\n  )\n\n  (:goal\n    (and\n      ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    place step - object\n    disk peg - place\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n\n    ;; true iff nothing is directly on top of this place (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b\n    (smaller ?a - disk ?b - disk)\n\n    ;; step sequencing control: exactly one action consumes the current step token and produces its successor\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    (succ ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto an empty peg.\n  ;; Requires the moved disk to be top (clear) and advances the explicit step token.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination peg must be empty (no disk directly on it)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid vacuous moves (prevents moving a disk to the place it is already on)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto another disk (must be larger and top).\n  ;; Requires the target disk to be the top disk and strictly larger; advances the explicit step token.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination disk must be top (clear) and strictly larger\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid vacuous moves (prevents moving a disk onto itself or onto its current support)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-6)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    disk peg place step\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n\n    ;; true iff nothing is directly on top of this place (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller a b) means a is strictly smaller than b\n    (smaller ?a - disk ?b - disk)\n\n    ;; step sequencing control: exactly one action consumes the current step token and produces its successor\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    (succ ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto an empty peg.\n  ;; Requires the moved disk to be top and advances the explicit step token.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination peg must be empty (no disk directly on it)\n      (clear ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid vacuous moves (prevents moving a disk to the place it is already on)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a support (peg or disk) onto another disk (must be larger and top).\n  ;; Requires the target disk to be the top disk and strictly larger; advances the explicit step token.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (at-step ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n\n      ;; disk is directly on ?from and is the top disk\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; destination disk must be top (clear) and strictly larger\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; forbid vacuous moves (prevents moving a disk onto itself or onto its current support)\n      (not (on ?d ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate the disk\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; former support becomes clear; destination no longer clear\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance step token so exactly one action occurs per step\n      (not (at-step ?s))\n      (at-step ?snext)\n    )\n  )\n)",

actions and predicates use places for supports.)\n    ;; Map disks and peg-places by equality through facts: we assert that peg places have no disk on them initially except where specified.\n\n    ;; initial clearness: top disk da is clear; empty peg places are clear\n    (clear da)\n    (clear p_peg_left) (clear p_peg_right)\n\n    ;; static size ordering (all necessary pairs a < b)\n    (smaller da db) (smaller da dc) (smaller da dd) (smaller da de) (smaller da df)\n    (smaller db dc) (smaller db dd) (smaller db de) (smaller db df)\n    (smaller dc dd) (smaller dc de) (smaller dc df)\n    (smaller dd de) (smaller dd df)\n    (smaller de df)\n\n    ;; Connect peg objects to their place aliases by asserting that the pegs correspond to these place objects.\n    ;; The domain's actions operate over places; to allow the planner to use named pegs, we include the following facts\n    ;; which identify the intended place objects for each peg name.\n    ;; We use (on ?d ?p) where ?p must be a place; p_peg_* are those place objects.\n    ;; There is no separate predicate linking pegs to places; the naming convention here provides the required place objects.\n    ;; (No additional facts needed beyond using the p_peg_* names as place objects.)\n  )\n\n  (:goal\n    (and\n      ;; final tower must be on right peg place with same ordering df bottom -> da top\n      (on da db)\n      (on db dc)\n      (on dc dd)\n      (on dd de)\n      (on de df)\n      (on df p_peg_right)\n\n      ;; left and middle peg places must be empty (clear)\n      (clear p_peg_left)\n      (clear p_peg_mid)\n\n      ;; require the final stage to have been reached (exactly 63 single-disk moves)\n      (at-step s63)\n    )\n  )\n)",

PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 6 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.
The left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 6 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, and disk F, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.
The left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]

FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types
    place
    disk - place
    peg  - place
  )

  (:predicates
    ;; disk d is immediately supported by place p (p is either a peg or another disk)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; nothing is on top of place p (so p is available as a destination)
    (clear ?p - place)
    ;; size ordering: (smaller d1 d2) means d1 is strictly smaller than d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a top disk ?d from some supporter ?from (a peg or a disk)
  ;; onto an empty peg ?to.
  (:action move-to-empty-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)     ;; ?d is immediately on ?from (so ?from is the support)
      (clear ?d)        ;; ?d is the top disk on its stack (nothing on top of it)
      (clear ?to)       ;; the target peg has nothing on it (empty)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      ;; the former supporter ?from now has nothing on it (becomes clear)
      (clear ?from)
      ;; the target peg is no longer clear because ?d is now on it
      (not (clear ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk ?d from some supporter ?from onto a top disk ?to (which must be larger).
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)     ;; ?d is immediately on ?from
      (clear ?d)        ;; ?d is top on its stack
      (clear ?to)       ;; ?to has nothing on it (so you place on top of ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)  ;; size constraint: cannot place larger on smaller
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      ;; the former supporter ?from becomes clear (nothing directly on it anymore)
      (clear ?from)
      ;; the new supporter ?to is not clear anymore
      (not (clear ?to))
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-3disks)
  (:domain hanoi)

  (:objects
    disk1 disk2 disk3 - disk
    pegA pegB pegC     - peg
  )

  ;; Initial state: all three disks stacked on pegA (disk3 largest bottom,
  ;; disk2 middle, disk1 smallest top). pegB and pegC are empty.
  (:init
    ;; immediate supports (on)
    (on disk3 pegA)
    (on disk2 disk3)
    (on disk1 disk2)

    ;; clear (nothing on top of these places)
    (clear disk1)   ;; top-most disk has nothing on it
    (clear pegB)
    (clear pegC)

    ;; size ordering (strict)
    (smaller disk1 disk2)
    (smaller disk1 disk3)
    (smaller disk2 disk3)
  )

  ;; Goal: whole stack moved to pegC with exact stacking order preserved,
  ;; and explicit final clear statuses fixed so these terminal conditions are enforced.
  (:goal (and
    ;; desired stack on pegC
    (on disk3 pegC)
    (on disk2 disk3)
    (on disk1 disk2)

    ;; explicit terminal clear states:
    ;; pegA and pegB must be empty in the final state
    (clear pegA)
    (clear pegB)
    ;; pegC must have something on it (i.e., not clear)
    (not (clear pegC))
    ;; disk1 is the top disk (nothing on it), disk2 and disk3 have disks on them
    (clear disk1)
    (not (clear disk2))
    (not (clear disk3))
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types
    place
    disk - place
    peg  - place
  )

  (:predicates
    ;; disk d is immediately supported by place p (p is either a peg or another disk)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; nothing is on top of place p (so p is available as a destination)
    (clear ?p - place)
    ;; size ordering: (smaller d1 d2) means d1 is strictly smaller than d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a top disk ?d from some supporter ?from (a peg or a disk)
  ;; onto an empty peg ?to.
  (:action move-to-empty-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)     ;; ?d is immediately on ?from (so ?from is the support)
      (clear ?d)        ;; ?d is the top disk on its stack (nothing on top of it)
      (clear ?to)       ;; the target peg has nothing on it (empty)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      ;; the former supporter ?from now has nothing on it (becomes clear)
      (clear ?from)
      ;; the target peg is no longer clear because ?d is now on it
      (not (clear ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk ?d from some supporter ?from onto a top disk ?to (which must be larger).
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)     ;; ?d is immediately on ?from
      (clear ?d)        ;; ?d is top on its stack
      (clear ?to)       ;; ?to has nothing on it (so you place on top of ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)  ;; size constraint: cannot place larger on smaller
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      ;; the former supporter ?from becomes clear (nothing directly on it anymore)
      (clear ?from)
      ;; the new supporter ?to is not clear anymore
      (not (clear ?to))
    )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-3disks)
  (:domain hanoi)

  (:objects
    disk1 disk2 disk3 - disk
    pegA pegB pegC     - peg
  )

  ;; Initial state: all three disks stacked on pegA (disk3 largest bottom,
  ;; disk2 middle, disk1 smallest top). pegB and pegC are empty.
  (:init
    ;; immediate supports (on)
    (on disk3 pegA)
    (on disk2 disk3)
    (on disk1 disk2)

    ;; clear (nothing on top of these places)
    (clear disk1)   ;; top-most disk has nothing on it
    (clear pegB)
    (clear pegC)

    ;; size ordering (strict)
    (smaller disk1 disk2)
    (smaller disk1 disk3)
    (smaller disk2 disk3)
  )

  ;; Goal: whole stack moved to pegC with exact stacking order preserved,
  ;; and explicit final clear statuses fixed so these terminal conditions are enforced.
  (:goal (and
    ;; desired stack on pegC
    (on disk3 pegC)
    (on disk2 disk3)
    (on disk1 disk2)

    ;; explicit terminal clear states:
    ;; pegA and pegB must be empty in the final state
    (clear pegA)
    (clear pegB)
    ;; pegC must have something on it (i.e., not clear)
    (not (clear pegC))
    ;; disk1 is the top disk (nothing on it), disk2 and disk3 have disks on them
    (clear disk1)
    (not (clear disk2))
    (not (clear disk3))
  ))
)
================================================================================

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    place\n    disk - place\n    peg  - place\n    stage\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; immediate support relation: disk is immediately on place (peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ;; no disk on top of place (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller ?d1 ?d2) means ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n    ;; stage successor relation (static)\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    ;; the current global stage (exactly one holds initially and actions preserve uniqueness)\n    (current ?s - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; update clear statuses for affected places\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance stage token (serializes actions)\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk ?d from supporter ?from onto a top disk ?to (which must be larger).\n  ;; Also advances the global stage token.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)       ;; update support\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; update clear statuses for affected places\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n\n      ;; advance stage token (serializes actions)\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    place\n    disk - place\n    peg  - place\n    stage\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)         ;; immediate support: disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)               ;; nothing is on top of place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)  ;; static strict size ordering: ?d1 is smaller than ?d2\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)   ;; ordered successor relation between stages\n    (current ?s - stage)             ;; unique current global stage token\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk ?d from supporter ?from (peg or disk) to an empty peg ?to.\n  ;; Advances stage token from ?s to its successor ?s2.\n  (:action move-to-empty-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)        ;; ?d is the top disk on its supporter\n      (clear ?to)       ;; destination peg must be clear (no disk on top)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      (clear ?from)        ;; supporter becomes clear (no disk on top)\n      (not (clear ?to))    ;; destination peg now has a disk on top\n\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk ?d from supporter ?from (peg or disk) onto top disk ?to (which must be larger).\n  ;; Advances stage token from ?s to its successor ?s2.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)         ;; ?d is the top disk on its supporter\n      (clear ?to)        ;; ?to must be top on its supporter to receive ?d\n      (smaller ?d ?to)   ;; size ordering: ?d strictly smaller than ?to\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      (clear ?from)       ;; supporter becomes clear (no disk on top)\n      (not (clear ?to))   ;; receiver ?to now has ?d on top, so ?to is not clear\n\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types\n    place stage\n    disk peg - place\n  )\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (disk or peg)\n    (clear ?p - place)              ; place ?p has no disk directly on it\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk) ; ?d1 is smaller than ?d2\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)  ; temporal successor relation between stages\n    (current ?s - stage)            ; which stage is the current one\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from some place onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-to-empty-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)       ; disk ?d is on ?from\n      (clear ?d)          ; ?d has nothing on top (top disk)\n      (clear ?to)         ; destination peg is empty on top\n      (current ?s)        ; we are at stage ?s\n      (succ ?s ?s2)       ; next stage is ?s2\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)       ; after removing ?d, the place it was on becomes clear\n      (not (clear ?to))   ; after placing ?d, the destination is not clear\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from some place onto another disk (must be larger).\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)       ; disk ?d is on ?from\n      (clear ?d)          ; ?d has nothing on top (top disk)\n      (clear ?to)         ; target disk has nothing on top (top)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)    ; moving disk must be smaller than the target disk\n      (current ?s)        ; we are at stage ?s\n      (succ ?s ?s2)       ; next stage is ?s2\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (clear ?from)       ; place we removed ?d from becomes clear\n      (not (clear ?to))   ; target disk now has ?d on top, therefore not clear\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi-6disks)\n  (:domain hanoi)\n\n  (:objects\n    diska diskb diskc diskd diske diskf - disk\n    peg_left peg_middle peg_right      - peg\n\n    stage0 stage1 stage2 stage3 stage4 stage5 stage6 stage7 stage8 stage9\n    stage10 stage11 stage12 stage13 stage14 stage15 stage16 stage17 stage18 stage19\n    stage20 stage21 stage22 stage23 stage24 stage25 stage26 stage27 stage28 stage29\n    stage30 stage31 stage32 stage33 stage34 stage35 stage36 stage37 stage38 stage39\n    stage40 stage41 stage42 stage43 stage44 stage45 stage46 stage47 stage48 stage49\n    stage50 stage51 stage52 stage53 stage54 stage55 stage56 stage57 stage58 stage59\n    stage60 stage61 stage62 stage63 - stage\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;;
